<abstract>
<variablelist>
<varlistentry>
<term>WHAT?</term>
<listitem>
<para>
From basic system call monitoring, over library dependency tracking to detecting memory leaks, these tools enable you to perform a number of debugging and profiling tasks in an efficient way.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term>WHY?</term>
<listitem>
<para>
This article is intended to provide a complete overview of application profiling and debugging tasks that can be performed using &productnameshort; tracing utilities.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term>EFFORT</term>
<listitem>
<para>
The average reading time of this article is approximately 30 minutes.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term>GOAL</term>
<listitem>
<para>
You will be able to profile, trace, and debug your applications using &productnameshort; tracing utilities.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term>REQUIREMENTS</term>
<listitem>
<para>
To trace and analyze system processes using these utilities, you must have &sudo; privileges and an adjusted ptrace_scope kernel configuration.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
</variablelist>
